<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-21-0399 </DOCNO><TEXT>An outline is given of the seminar presentation. Topics covered includethe general principles which provide a defense for non-performance dueto supervening events; the legal principles which establish strict standardsfor the party seeking protection; the employment of all reasonable meansto avoid the impact of the supervening event; and court-adjusted contracts.The reader is referred to specific lawsuits for illustration of eachpoint.</TEXT></DOC>